<Folder><name>Scenic Points</name><Placemark><name>Baguio</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[Summer capital of the Philippines (1,400 m). Built 1900s by the American colonial government as a hill station. Burnham Park, Session Road; cool weather; Igorot crafts at the Maharlika and Easter Weaving School.]]></description><Point><coordinates>120.596000,16.402300,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Atok / Halsema highway</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[The road's high point at ~2,255 m — once the highest road in the Philippines. Vegetable terraces stair-step down both sides; cabbages, lettuce, broccoli. Strawberries (and strawberry taho — silken tofu in syrup) sold at Mount Pulag turnoff.]]></description><Point><coordinates>120.739700,16.577800,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Sagada</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[Pine-forest village famous for hanging coffins still installed by the Kankanaey on cliffs at Echo Valley. Sumaguing cave (helmets, headlamps, guides) is a strenuous 2-hour wade through underground rivers.]]></description><Point><coordinates>120.900000,17.085600,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Bontoc</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[Provincial capital. Bontoc Museum is a hidden gem — old photographs of headhunting expeditions, original textiles, a reconstructed traditional Bontoc village in the courtyard.]]></description><Point><coordinates>120.975600,16.977800,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Banaue</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[Main viewpoint town for the rice terraces — but the most-photographed terraces (the 'amphitheater') are at Batad, 12 km on. Banaue town itself is a strung-out highway settlement; sleep at Batad if you can.]]></description><Point><coordinates>121.059400,16.921400,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Batad rice terraces</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[Amphitheater of stone-walled terraces around a small village reachable only on foot from the road end. Walk down through the terraces, stay overnight in a homestay, hike out to the Tappiya waterfall (1 hr down). UNESCO World Heritage.]]></description><Point><coordinates>121.126400,16.929200,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark></Folder>
